<link rel="stylesheet" href="/public/stylesheets/client-hints.css">
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Client Hints</h1>

<h2>Request Headers</h2>
<pre><code>{{ requestHeaders | json }}</code></pre>

<h2>Response Headers</h2>
<pre><code>{{ responseHeaders | json }}</code></pre>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<p>There's a <code>Accept-CH</code> response header set for this page. aResources on this page and subsequent navigation request will include specified <code>sec-ch-*</code> headers. Steps to check:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Open DevTools and switch to Network tag.</li>
  <li>Click <code>client-hints.css</code> and <code>mountain.webp</code>, there should be additional <code>sec-ch-*</code> request headers set.</li>
  <li>Refresh the page, click <code>/client-hints</code>, this top-level request will also include these headers.</li>
</ol>

